title: Compiler error

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

body:
### Code ```Rust #[tokio::main] async fn main() { util::bootstrap(); let config = config::get_config().await; let task_factory = Arc::new(tasks::TaskFactory::new(config).await); &task_factory.create_async_jobs().await; } pub struct TaskFactory { config: Arc>, sched: Arc, job_map: HashMap, } impl TaskFactory { pub async fn new(config: Arc>) -> Self { TaskFactory { config, sched: Arc::new(JobScheduler::new().await.unwrap()), job_map: HashMap::new(), } } pub async fn create_async_jobs(&mut self) { let fs_job = Job::new("0 15 6,8,10 * Mar,Jun Fri 2017", |_uuid, _lock| { let _ = Box::new(async move { println!("{:?} Hi I ran", chrono::Utc::now()); }); }) .unwrap(); let fs_id = self.sched.add(fs_job).await; self.job_map .insert(JobKey::FsWatcher, fs_id.unwrap().to_owned()); tokio::spawn(self.sched.start()); } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.66.0-nightly (1898c34e9 2022-10-26) binary: rustc commit-hash:
